(Reuters) -New York City Mayor Eric Adams on Thursday said his first paycheck, to arrive on Friday, will be automatically converted into cryptocurrency via Coinbase Global Inc. -  The salary will be converted to ethereum and bitcoin, the statement added.

The mayor last year said he would take his first three paychecks in bitcoin https://www.reuters.com/world/us/new-york-mayor-elect-eric-adams-says-he-will-take-his-first-paychecks-bitcoin-2021-11-04 and signaled his intention to make his city the ‚Äúcenter of the cryptocurrency industry‚Äù.

‚ÄúNew York is the center of the world, and we want it to be the center of cryptocurrency and other financial innovations,‚Äù Adams said in a statement.

By Ardee Napolitano -  CALAIS, France (Reuters) ‚Äì     Eric Zemmour, the French far-right presidential challenger, on Wednesday said he would seize back control of France‚Äôs borders from Europe, block European Union free trade negotiations and prevent any further enlargement of the bloc to the east.

Pitching his vision for France‚Äôs relationship with the EU, Zemmour rubbished President Emmanuel Macron‚Äôs quest for deeper European cooperation as a folly that put the needs of French citizens in the hands of an illegitimate Brussels elite.

‚ÄúI want France to be in Europe, but I want France to come before Europe,‚Äù Zemmour said in a speech delivered on a wind-swept point near the northern port of Calais, from where thousands of illegal migrants try each year to reach Britain.
